		<item>
		<title>3 Tricks to Localize Your Google Ads (With Examples!)</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/localize-google-ads</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Mark Irvine]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 09 Apr 2024 18:49:56 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Google Ads]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=81754</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Use these three key strategies to make your Google Ads more appealing to local customers.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/localize-google-ads">3 Tricks to Localize Your Google Ads (With Examples!)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Local businesses know how important it is to be found in their communities when users search online. However, it can be difficult for small local businesses to compete with national brands that can afford to outspend them on Google Ads. Instead, local businesses need to be smarter and make the most of targeting their local area within Google Ads.</p>
<p>But local advertisers have some powerful tools when it comes to advertising online. More than <a href="https://www.ipx1031.com/small-business-statistics-report/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">80%</a> of consumers would prefer to shop locally‚Äìand nearly 60% would even pay more to support a local business! Savvy advertisers can take advantage of this and highlight their local status when customers are searching for their products and services online.</p>
<p>In fact, Google Ads and Microsoft Ads have several features that any local business should take advantage of to have their ads stand out in their local searches. So, here are my top three strategies for localizing search ads.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ol>
<li><a href="#local-dynamic-keyword-insertion">Dynamically insert locations in your Responsive Search Ads</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-ads-location-assets">Create location assets (and optimize your Google Business Profile)</a></li>
<li><a href="#google-ads-assets-for-local-ads">Take advantage of other local ad assets</a></li>
</ol>
<h2>How to localize your Google Ads</h2>
<p>Here are three ways any business can localize its <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/promotions-in-google-ads">Google Ads</a>.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Looking for other ways to get more out of your local campaigns? Try our free <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Grader </a>to get an instant read on key metrics plus optimization ideas.</p>
<div id="local-dynamic-keyword-insertion"></div>
<h3>1. Dynamically insert locations in your Responsive Search Ads</h3>
<p>Of course,<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/12/15/local-marketing-ideas" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> localizing your ad copy</a> for each city, town, or state you serve is a clear and effective way to show your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/02/06/online-reputation-management">business is local</a> to your searchers. But, manually creating hundreds of ads for every town where people might search for your services will quickly get time-consuming. Plus, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-search-partner-insights">targeting</a> each one in its own campaign? A nightmare in the making for your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/10/google-ads-account-structure" target="_blank" rel="noopener">account structure</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ad-example.jpg" alt="local google ads - example of google ads for different cities" width="642" height="445" class="aligncenter wp-image-81853 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ad-example.jpg 642w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ad-example-480x333.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 642px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Instead of manually adjusting each ad for every city, you can <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-performance-max-updates-2024">tailor your ads</a> easily by using <a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/9773001?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">dynamic location insertion</a> in your Responsive Search Ads. Dynamic location insertion works almost identically to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/04/17/dynamic-keyword-insertion-guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google‚Äôs Dynamic Keyword Insertion</a>, just instead of inserting the keyword directly into your ad‚Äôs text, these ads will automatically be customized to your user‚Äôs location.</p>
<p>To get started with Dynamic Location Insertion in your RSAs, simply write a new headline or description in an RSA. You can insert the location anywhere in the headline or description (just be mindful of character limits). As you type out your new message, when you‚Äôre ready to dynamically insert the location in your text, hit the<strong> {</strong> open bracket to trigger the prompt below, then select ‚Äúlocation insertion‚Äù from the drop-down menu.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ads-dynamic-keyword-insertion.jpg" alt="local google ads - example of adding dynamic keywords in the Google Ads ad editor" width="432" height="345" class="aligncenter wp-image-81859 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ads-dynamic-keyword-insertion.jpg 432w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ads-dynamic-keyword-insertion-300x240.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 432px) 100vw, 432px" /></p>
<p>From here, Google what type of location you want your ads to highlight. Within the United States, your locations should be formatted as a city, state, or country. Effectively, this tells Google how ‚Äúlocal‚Äù you want to highlight yourself. A searcher from Boston, Massachusetts, for instance, would read an ad differently depending on how this location was formatted.</p>
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td width="312">Location format</td>
<td width="312">Ad Text Inserted</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="312">LOCATION(City)</td>
<td width="312">Boston</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="312">LOCATION(State)</td>
<td width="312">Massachusetts</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="312">LOCATION(Country)</td>
<td width="312">United States of America</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>Outside the US, advertisers can either show the city or country. Unfortunately, local international equivalents like provinces or prefectures aren‚Äôt yet supported.</p>
<p>Finally, there‚Äôs a final option to include ‚Äúdefault text‚Äù within your dynamic location insertion parameter. This default text will only show when Google can‚Äôt insert the name of the searcher‚Äôs location directly in the ad text. This might happen due to character limits or if Google can‚Äôt easily identify the exact location of a searcher.</p>
<p>This headline might read &#8220;Proudly Serving {LOCATION(City): Your City}&#8221; when you see it in Google Ads. But Google will dynamically change it to read ‚Äúproudly serving Boston‚Äù or ‚Äúproudly serving Cambridge‚Äù when users search from those locations. But when someone from a long-named place like Manchester-by-the-Sea searches for you, your ad will use the default text and simply read ‚Äúproudly serving your city.‚Äù</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4cd.png" alt="üìç" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Is your Google Ads account structure optimized for local ads? Find out using our free guide to the perfect <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLAccountStructure.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_LastAccountStructureGuide_Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads account structure</a>.</p>
<div id="google-ads-location-assets"></div>
<h3>2. Create location assets (optimize your Google Business Profile)</h3>
<p>The first absolute must-do for any local business is to claim, complete, and keep their <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/03/google-my-business-optimization" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Business Profile</a> (GBP) up to date! This helps customers searching for your business, and will also hugely improve your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/10/12/local-seo" target="_blank" rel="noopener">local SEO</a> to help you stand out from your competitors on the SERP. But your GBP can also help you with your PPC results as well. You can link your Google Business Profile directly to your ads and create <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2011/09/19/adwords-location-extensions-guide#:~:text=Location%20extensions%20allow%20you%20to,is%20a%20pretty%20powerful%20option." target="_blank" rel="noopener">location assets (formerly location extensions).</a></p>
<p>With location assets, your text ads will highlight your local business address(es) and current hours to local searchers. On mobile devices, searchers will also have the option to call your local branch from the SERP directly. Clicking on the address will open up your full Google Business Profile and allow searchers to get directions or begin navigating to your branch in Google Maps.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/localized-google-ads-assets.jpg" alt="how to localize google ads - example of a location asset" width="751" height="255" class="aligncenter wp-image-81858 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/localized-google-ads-assets.jpg 751w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/localized-google-ads-assets-480x163.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 751px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Additionally, once you‚Äôve enabled location assets within your campaigns, your Google Business Profile may occasionally show at the top of the local map pack as a prominent sponsored listing with extra lines of text to distinguish you from other local businesses.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ads-google-business-profile.jpg" alt="local google ads - google business profile ad examples" width="804" height="456" class="aligncenter wp-image-81857 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ads-google-business-profile.jpg 804w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ads-google-business-profile-480x272.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 804px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Recently, Google also started rolling out <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/07/google-ads-location-assets-enhancements" target="_blank" rel="noopener">additional enhancements to its location assets</a>, such as automatically highlighting your GBP‚Äôs cover photo alongside your text ads.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/localize-google-ads-google-business-profile-and-ad.jpg" alt="local google ads - screenshot of google business profile images in ads " width="677" height="434" class="aligncenter wp-image-81856 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/localize-google-ads-google-business-profile-and-ad.jpg 677w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/localize-google-ads-google-business-profile-and-ad-480x308.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 677px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>These advantages aren‚Äôt unique to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-scripts">optimizing</a> just your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ad-strength">Google Ads</a> though. Microsoft Advertising has similar location extensions. Unlike Google Ads, you don‚Äôt need to link your GBP or Bing Places account to Microsoft Advertising to use location extensions. You can enter each location‚Äôs address and hours within Microsoft Advertising to enable this feature. Additionally, Microsoft also recently launched <a href="https://www.searchenginejournal.com/microsoft-launches-local-search-ads-for-bing/481731/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Local Search Ads for Bing</a>, which highlights advertisers&#8217; location extensions in local map results.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-microsoft-ads-example.jpg" alt="local microsoft ads - example of bing places ads" width="461" height="498" class="aligncenter wp-image-81855 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-microsoft-ads-example.jpg 461w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-microsoft-ads-example-278x300.jpg 278w" sizes="(max-width: 461px) 100vw, 461px" /></p>
<div id="google-ads-assets-for-local-ads"></div>
<h3>3. Take advantage of other local ad assets</h3>
<p>Although location assets are the most well-known asset for local advertisers, there are several other assets that can also be used to add a local flair to your PPC ads. <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/09/03/structured-snippets" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Structured snippets</a>, for instance, can complement your ads with a list of neighborhoods that your business serves.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/localize-google-ads-callout-assets.jpg" alt="local google ads - example of google ad using structured snippet" width="780" height="232" class="aligncenter wp-image-81854 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/localize-google-ads-callout-assets.jpg 780w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/localize-google-ads-callout-assets-480x143.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 780px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>To set up neighborhood structured snippets, simply create a new structured snippet asset and choose the ‚Äúneighborhood‚Äù header. Then proceed to list at least three neighborhoods or areas that you serve as ‚Äúvalues.‚Äù Generally, these values will appear in the same order that you enter them here, so prioritize your top neighborhoods in the first positions to maximize their effectiveness and visibility. Your neighborhood structured snippets can still appear alongside other structured snippets used to highlight your services, brands, models, and other headers.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/localized-google-ads-headline.jpg" alt="local google ads - local headline examples " width="600" height="633" class="aligncenter wp-image-81861 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/localized-google-ads-headline.jpg 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/localized-google-ads-headline-480x506.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Sitelinks can also be incredibly useful to help highlight your local ads. If you service different areas and have a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/great-landing-pages" target="_blank" rel="noopener">dedicated landing page</a> for each area or office, these can easily be utilized as highly visible sitelinks that both spotlight your local experience and help send local searchers to the most relevant page.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ads-sitelinks.jpg" alt="local google ads - sitelinks for locations example" width="842" height="240" class="aligncenter wp-image-81860 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ads-sitelinks.jpg 842w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ads-sitelinks-480x137.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 842px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Finally, don‚Äôt overlook the small but versatile <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2014/09/08/adwords-callout-extensions" target="_blank" rel="noopener">callout assets</a>! With up to 25 characters of text each, these assets are flexible and easy ways to call out unique pieces of your business. Differentiate yourself from national brands by including callouts like ‚Äúlocal family owned,‚Äù ‚Äúserving Boston since 1989,‚Äù ‚Äúlocal experts,‚Äù and other similar messages to add some local flair to your ads.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ads-ad-assets.png" alt="local google ads - google ad callout assets screenshot" width="530" height="234" class="aligncenter wp-image-81851 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ads-ad-assets.png 530w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-google-ads-ad-assets-480x212.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 530px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Bing has some <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/02/25/bings-ads-vs-google-adwords" target="_blank" rel="noopener">additional unique features</a> that Google doesn‚Äôt have for your ads. Hidden deep among your account level settings, there‚Äôs the ability to opt-in to Microsoft Advertising‚Äôs <a href="https://about.ads.microsoft.com/en-us/blog/post/september-2021/show-your-brand-values-marketing-with-purpose-business-attributes" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Marketing with Purpose Business Attributes</a>. These attributes allow advertisers to share how their brand takes pride in different aspects as it relates to community responsibility, accessibility, environmental responsibility, and inclusivity. Among these attributes that advertisers can highlight for their brand are &#8220;small business‚Äù and &#8220;local business.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-microsoft-ad-attributions.jpg" alt="local microsoft ads - screenshot of microsoft ad attribution options" width="889" height="385" class="aligncenter wp-image-81850 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-microsoft-ad-attributions.jpg 889w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-microsoft-ad-attributions-480x208.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 889px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>You may choose any relevant attributes for your brand within the &#8220;marketing with purpose&#8221; business attributes. Once applied to your account, your ads will sometimes show with a relevant attribute highlighted next to them, such as below.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-microsoft-ad-example.jpg" alt="local microsoft ads - example of a microsoft ad taking advantage of attributes" width="832" height="177" class="aligncenter wp-image-81852 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-microsoft-ad-example.jpg 832w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/local-microsoft-ad-example-480x102.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 832px, 100vw" /></p>
<h2>Write your PPC ads like a local</h2>
<p>Big budgets or not‚Äìyou‚Äôve got the local advantage when it comes to advertising on the SERP. Take pride and highlight yourself as a local business within your PPC ads. Not only will searchers support you, but most are going to prefer to engage with your ad over the generic brands that you‚Äôre competing against. If you try these ideas but still want more out of your localized ads, see how <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/marketing-services?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Demo_Blog_Demo" target="_blank" rel="noopener">our solutions</a> can help you maximize your campaigns no matter how near or far your customers are!</p>
