		<item>
		<title>Google Releases New Local Services Ads Metrics to Measure Reach</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-local-services-ads-new-metrics</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Mark Irvine]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 04 Mar 2024 12:30:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Google Ads]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=80993</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Google started rolling out new metrics to help you measure Local Services Ads. Find out what they are and how to use them.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-local-services-ads-new-metrics">Google Releases New Local Services Ads Metrics to Measure Reach</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Location matters when you‚Äôre searching online. Whether you‚Äôre searching for a plumber, repairman, or even a lawyer‚Äìwe aren‚Äôt looking to connect with someone several states away. Optimizing your business to show for these local searches is critical‚Äìand since 2015, many advertisers have taken advantage of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/06/11/google-local-service-ads">Google‚Äôs Local Services Ads</a> as part of their strategy to be found by customers in their area.</p>
<p>However, Google previously offered little data or insight into how often Local Services Ads (LSAs) were shown on the SERP, and advertisers had very little opportunity to troubleshoot and optimize their LSAs. Thankfully, Google recently started sharing new ad impression and impression share metrics with advertisers which can help guide you to make the most of your Local Services Ads.</p>
<h3>Table of contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#what-are-google-local-services-ads">What are Google Local Services Ads?</a></li>
<li><a href="#new-google-local-services-ads-metrics">New Google Local Services Ads metrics</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#google-lsas-ad-impressions">Ad impressions</a></li>
<li><a href="#top-impressions-rate-on-search">Top impression rate on search</a></li>
<li><a href="#absolute-top-impression-rate-on-search">Absolute top impression rate on search</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<div id="what-are-google-local-services-ads"></div>
<h2>What are Google Local Services Ads?</h2>
<p>Google Local Services Ads are a simple (and safe!) way to connect local searchers to professionals in their area (like dog walkers and <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/roofing-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">roofers</a>). This unique local ad format highlights locally screened professionals that are ready to take on their job at the very top of the SERP. Over the years, Google has opened these Local Services Ads to over 80 <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/05/15/google-ads-benchmarks">different local industries</a>‚Äìfrom <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/home-services-promotion-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">home services</a>, car repair, pet care, accountants, lawyers, and more. Local Services Ads are available in the US, Canada, the United Kingdom, and several European countries.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/06/11/google-local-service-ads">Local Services Ads</a> appear above the traditional paid search ads and organic listings‚Äìand advertisers can take advantage of running both LSAs and traditional PPC ads simultaneously, often showing up twice for the same search.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/google-local-services-ads-vs-google-ads.webp" alt="screenshot of google local services ads vs google ads" width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-81003" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/google-local-services-ads-vs-google-ads.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/google-local-services-ads-vs-google-ads-480x308.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Unlike traditional paid search ads though‚ÄìLocal Services Ads have no keywords or <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/06/06/negative-keyword-guide">negative keywords</a> to manage. LSA advertisers simply select the types of jobs they want to show ads for, and Google matches your listing to relevant search terms. Additionally, Google Local Services Ads charges advertisers a fee for each lead (usually a call or message) from their ads, whereas traditional paid search campaigns <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/05/21/how-much-does-adwords-cost">charge advertisers</a> for each ad click to their website‚Äôs <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/great-landing-pages">landing page</a>, regardless of whether they contact that business.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="üõë" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Worried you&#8217;re wasting spend in Google Ads? Find out with a free, instant audit &gt;&gt; <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader">Google Ads Performance Grader</a></p>
<div id="new-google-local-services-ads-metrics"></div>
<h2>New Google Local Services Ads metrics</h2>
<p>Previously, Local Services advertisers could review very limited data on their ads‚Äô performance. You can view your leads and your total costs during any given time frame‚Äìbut apart from that, very little else. Since November 2023, Google has been rolling out new impression and Impression rate metrics for your Local Services Ads. Advertisers can view these metrics under the ‚Äúreports‚Äù tab in the left-hand menu of the Local Services Ads interface.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/google-local-services-ads-metrics.webp" alt="google local services ads dashboard" width="936" height="510" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-81020" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/google-local-services-ads-metrics.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/google-local-services-ads-metrics-480x262.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Local Services Ads now include metrics for your ad impressions, top impression rate on search, and absolute top impression rate on search.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6a8.png" alt="üö®" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> What results can you expect from Google Ads? Download our latest <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteGoogleAdsBenchmarks2023.html?cid=Web_WS_incontent_guide_2023benchmarks_Download&amp;utm_source=wordstream&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=incontent_links">Google Ads Benchmarks</a> to find out!</p>
<div id="google-lsas-ad-impressions"></div>
<h3>Ad impressions</h3>
<p>Simply put, ad <a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/6320?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">impressions</a> tell you how many times your LSAs were shown on the SERP. Getting seen on Google is important and your ad impressions is a metric to quantify your ads‚Äô <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/search-visibility/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">visibility</a>.</p>
<p>But like other search ad formats‚Äìmost people who see your ad won‚Äôt click or become a lead. That‚Äôs fine and expected‚Äìand you don‚Äôt pay Google every time your LSAs show, only when someone clicks and becomes a lead.</p>
<p>Here are some ways to use the ad impressions metric.</p>
<p><strong>Troubleshoot your LSAs</strong></p>
<p>Previously, it could be tough for small businesses to know if their ads were even running if they <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/02/21/google-ads-not-converting">weren‚Äôt getting leads</a>. If you see zero ad impressions, that‚Äôs a sign that something with your profile isn‚Äôt set up correctly, or that your ads are paused.</p>
<p><strong>Understand your reach</strong></p>
<p>Lots of SMBs generally start their advertising campaigns small. That‚Äôs understandable, but oftentimes they reach a much smaller audience than they expected and get disappointed. This additional insight into the reach of your LSAs may encourage you to expand your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/10/17/google-ads-location-targeting">targeted locations</a> or include more job types in your listing.</p>
<p><strong>Improve your LSA engagement</strong></p>
<p>Remember that the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/05/15/google-ads-benchmarks">average search ad CTR is only 6%</a>! And unlike search ads, Local Service Ads push searchers to call or message the provider directly. As a result, LSAs may have far less engagement than the links from your search campaigns. You may only see that 0.2% of your ad impressions turn into a lead!</p>
<p>You can use your leads/impressions ratio as a proxy metric for your LSA engagement. If you see that people are seeing your LSAs but not engaging, it may be a sign that your LSA profile could use a refresh. Simply updating your <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-write-a-business-description/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">business bio</a> with new, competitive offers or uploading a fresh high-quality photo or headshot can make a huge difference in improving your Local Service Ads.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/26a1.png" alt="‚ö°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Is your Google Ads account set up for success? Download now &gt;&gt; <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLAccountStructure.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_LastAccountStructureGuide_Download">The Last Guide to Google Ads Account Structure You&#8217;ll Ever Need</a></p>
<div id="top-impressions-rate-on-search"></div>
<h3>Top impression rate on search</h3>
<p>Top impression rate on search tells you how often your LSAs show above the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/08/03/organic-traffic">organic search results</a>. The top impression rate on search is calculated as:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Search top impression rate = Impressions on top/Impressions</strong></p>
<p>Local Services Ads <em>nearly</em> always appear above the organic results. In my experience, this metric has always been 100% for my advertisers‚Äìbut it wouldn‚Äôt surprise me if Google was including this metric because it plans to start testing LSAs in different positions of the SERP or within its new <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/05/19/google-search-generative-experience">Search Generative Experience</a>.</p>
<p>Bear in mind though‚Äìthis metric is <strong>NOT</strong> the same as <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/06/07/impression-share">search impression share</a>, which measures how frequently your ad showed for relevant searches. Just because your ad is showing at the top doesn‚Äôt mean that you aren‚Äôt <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/02/14/google-ads-budgeting-strategies">missing potential ad impressions due to low budgets</a> or poor ranking.</p>
<div id="absolute-top-impression-rate-on-search"></div>
<h3>Absolute top impression rate on search</h3>
<p>Absolute top impression rate on search tells you how often your LSAs show in the very first spot on the SERP.¬† Absolute top impression rate on search is calculated as:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Search absolute top impression rate = Impressions in the first spot /Impressions</strong></p>
<p>Here are some ways you can use this metric.</p>
<p><strong>See how competitively your LSAs are performing</strong></p>
<p>Being in that very first spot will get you a lot of reach, attention, and engagement. But it can also be very expensive. If you see a low absolute top impression rate, it may be a sign to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/01/17/google-ads-bid-management">increase your bids</a>. But if you see a higher top impression rate, be sure that you‚Äôre comfortable with your current cost per lead. There‚Äôs no shame in being in a lower position if you can afford more profitable leads.</p>
<p><strong>Guide your LSA budget decisions</strong></p>
<p>Google allows businesses of all sizes and budgets to run LSAs‚Äìallowing them to set a weekly budget for their ads to run across the SERP. However, small businesses often fall into a trap‚Äìthey‚Äôre overly excited about showing up in that absolute top position but also have a relatively <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/home-services-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">small budget</a>.</p>
<p>Consequently, they can only afford a few (very expensive) leads before they run out of budget. It‚Äôs much better to afford more leads in a lower position at a better cost per lead when <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/04/11/google-local-services-ads-tips">managing an LSA on a smaller budget</a>.</p>
<p>If you‚Äôre consistently spending your weekly LSA budget and also have a high absolute top impression rate on search, you‚Äôre likely missing out on a lot of opportunities for your ads to show. Consider either increasing your budget or decreasing your bids if you run into this dilemma.</p>
<p>To help benchmark what leads for your business cost on LSAs, consider using Google‚Äôs <a href="https://ads.google.com/local-services-ads/cost/#!/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LSA budget estimator tool</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/google-local-services-ads-budget-estimator.webp" alt="google local services ads budget estimator" width="936" height="585" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-81021" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/google-local-services-ads-budget-estimator.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/google-local-services-ads-budget-estimator-480x300.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f440.png" alt="üëÄ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Want to learn more about search engine marketing on Google? Get the free guide &gt;&gt; <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLPPC101.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_PPC101_Download">PPC 101: Complete Guide to Google Ads</a></p>
<h2>Start using Google Local Services Ads new metrics</h2>
<p>Google‚Äôs new impression and impression rate metrics for Local Services Ads can help provide helpful insight into managing these campaigns. <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/hvac-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Local service providers and</a> advertisers (like <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/contractor-leads/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">contractors</a>) can see the costs and leads of their LSA campaigns and begin to understand how their LSAs reach searchers and how best to optimize them. Learn more about <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/localize-google-ads">localizing Google ads</a> here.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-local-services-ads-new-metrics">Google Releases New Local Services Ads Metrics to Measure Reach</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>Is DuckDuckGo Legit? 5 Facts That Prove It Is</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/what-is-duckduckgo</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Mark Irvine]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 23 Jan 2024 12:30:49 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Marketing News & Insights]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=79518</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>DuckDuckGo might be DuckDuckComing for Google's market share. Here's what you need to know.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/what-is-duckduckgo">Is DuckDuckGo Legit? 5 Facts That Prove It Is</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Nearly everything we do online is tracked. That may not be a secret, but it‚Äôs certainly an uncomfortable reality for most. In a <a href="https://about.ads.microsoft.com/en-us/insights/g/in-brands-we-trust-the-intersection-of-privacy-and-trust-in-the-age-of-the-empowered-consumer" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2020 study</a>, 91% of respondents were concerned about the amount of data companies can collect about them. Today, we‚Äôre seeing legislation slowly catch up to these concerns, and Big Tech companies are rolling out new privacy solutions to minimize abuse and anonymize the data they collect from users. But consumers are still skeptical and frequently opting to find their own way to explore the web, privately.</p>
<p>This growing audience of privacy-minded searchers is increasingly abandoning Google for a search engine with this goal in mind, DuckDuckGo. So, is DuckDuckGo legit? If so, what do you need to know about it? We&#8217;re sharing all the answers.</p>
<h3>Table of contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#what-is-duckduckgo">What is DuckDuckGo?</a></li>
<li><a href="#duckduckgo-statistics">DuckDuckGo statistics and facts you need to know</a>
<ul>
<li><a href="#how-many-people-use-duckduckgo">How many people use DuckDuckGo?</a></li>
<li><a href="#who-uses-duckduckgo">Who uses DuckDuckGo?</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-do-people-search-on-duckduckgo">How do people search on DuckDuckGo?</a></li>
<li><a href="#where-do-people-use-duckduckgo">Where do they use DuckDuckGo?</a></li>
<li><a href="#are-people-using-only-duckduckgo">Are people using <em>only</em> DuckDuckGo?</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><a href="#how-to-advertise-on-duckduckgo">How can you advertise on DuckDuckGo?</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="what-is-duckduckgo"></div>
<h2>What is DuckDuckGo?</h2>
<p>DuckDuckGo is an emerging search engine that should look and feel similar to what users should expect from Google or Microsoft (although they&#8217;ve been around since 2008!). From DuckDuckGo.com, searchers can find answers to their queries collected from <a href="https://duckduckgo.com/duckduckgo-help-pages/results/sources/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">countless sources</a>, oftentimes indexed from their own crawler (DuckDuckBot.) More than just links‚Äîthe DuckDuckGo SERP includes common features like maps, weather, local business information, images, videos, shopping‚Äîand even ads.</p>
<p>And just like Google and Microsoft, DuckDuckGo also offers its own <a href="https://duckduckgo.com/app" target="_blank" rel="noopener">web browsers</a> for desktop and mobile devices and <a href="https://www.spreadprivacy.com/protect-your-inbox-with-duckduckgo-email-protection/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">free personal email</a> services. The suite of products from DuckDuckGo is very comparable to what most would expect from other major search networks.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/what-is-duckduckgo.webp" alt="screenshot of duckduckgo on mobile and desktop" width="936" height="578" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79523" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/what-is-duckduckgo.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/what-is-duckduckgo-480x296.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The key differentiator that DuckDuckGo highlights in its suite is its high focus on its user‚Äôs privacy. Unlike Google and Microsoft‚Äôs search engines, browsers, and other products‚ÄîDuckDuckGo does not create unique cookies, store your IP addresses, search and browsing history, or any other unique identifiers. DuckDuckGo has none of your personal information and therefore has never sold any personal information. DuckDuckGo is always encrypted, and privacy is its core value.</p>
<p>Most tech companies‚Äô privacy policies are tombs of legalese. <a href="https://duckduckgo.com/privacy?" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DuckDuckGo‚Äôs privacy policy</a> opens simply and shortly: ‚ÄúWe don‚Äôt track you. That‚Äôs our privacy policy in a nutshell.‚Äù</p>
<p>DuckDuckGo‚Äôs unique respect for its users&#8217; privacy has earned it more praise and attention over the past few years and it‚Äôs quickly emerging as more than just a niche tertiary search engine into a more prominent alternative to Google. As DuckDuckGo‚Äôs user base grows, so does its opportunity for savvy marketers to reach a very unique audience that are ditching Google.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="üõë" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Want to learn more about search engine marketing? <strong>Get the free guide &gt;&gt;</strong> <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLPPC101.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_PPC101_Download">PPC 101</a></p>
<div id="duckduckgo-statistics"></div>
<h2>5 DuckDuckGo statistics you need to know</h2>
<p>To learn more about this new audience, I‚Äôve collected several fascinating statistics from DuckDuckGo.</p>
<div id="how-many-people-use-duckduckgo"></div>
<h3>1. How many people use DuckDuckGo?</h3>
<p>When looking into DuckDuckGo, your first question is probably how many people use it? How often are they searching?</p>
<p>Today, 3.1 billion searches occur on DuckDuckGo every month. DuckDuckGo has grown its audience to over 46 million users around the world. And although that may be just a small fraction when compared to Google‚Äôs impressive reach‚Äîmany people who search on DuckDuckGo do so because they no longer trust Google with their data. 6.4 million users on DuckDuckGo can‚Äôt be reached on Google Search.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-statistics.webp" alt="three duckduckgo statistics" width="936" height="272" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79524" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-statistics.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-statistics-480x139.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="who-uses-duckduckgo"></div>
<h3>2. Who uses DuckDuckGo?</h3>
<p>Both Google and Bing see roughly a 50/50 split between male and female audiences. Interestingly‚ÄîDuckDuckGo has a slight skew along gender lines, with nearly 60% of their traffic from males.</p>
<p>The age demographics of DuckDuckGo users are similar to that of Google and Bing‚Äôs, with a small promising growth in the younger 18-24 age range.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-demographics.webp" alt="chart showing duckduckgo user demographics by gender" width="936" height="514" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79526" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-demographics.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-demographics-480x264.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The income distribution of DuckDuckGo‚Äôs audience is really where it shines to most marketers. DuckDuckGo attracts a small but very affluent audience. The median income in the US is about $44,000, but more than 85% of DuckDuckGo‚Äôs users make above that average income‚Äîwith over 60% of them making at least $100,000!</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-user-income.webp" alt="chart showing duckduckgo users by income" width="936" height="535" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79527" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-user-income.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-user-income-480x274.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="how-do-people-search-on-duckduckgo"></div>
<h3>3. How do people search on DuckDuckGo?</h3>
<p>Google prides itself on its ‚Äúmobile-first‚Äù mantra‚Äîand for the better half of the last decade, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/08/13/google-ads-mobile-benchmarks">mobile has made up most Google‚Äôs reach</a>. Microsoft‚Äîand it‚Äôs personal computing dominance‚Äîhas strongly cemented its own <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/11/19/who-uses-bing-anyway">Bing search engine as a major player in the desktop search market</a>. Privacy-focused DuckDuckGo users actively take their preferences across both devices. In the US, over 15 million searchers use DuckDuckGo on both desktop and mobile‚Äîwith less than 5 million using the privacy-focused search engine on just one device.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-unique-users.webp" alt="chart showing duckduckgo unique users by device" width="936" height="491" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79525" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-unique-users.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-unique-users-480x252.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Interestingly, these over 20 million mobile searchers help catapult <a href="https://radar.cloudflare.com/reports/searchengines-2023-q2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DuckDuckGo to the #2 search engine on mobile in the USA.</a> Still considerably behind Google‚Äôs massive mobile dominance, these 20 million users still make up a sizable population of the US market.</p>
<div id="where-do-people-use-duckduckgo"></div>
<h3>4. Where do people use DuckDuckGo?</h3>
<p>DuckDuckGo is headquartered in Pennsylvania and for most of its history has been an emerging competitor in the US Search Market. But as Google has struggled to calm privacy concerns across the globe, it has been successful in taking market share from the search giant in several major international markets. Today, DuckDuckGo makes up about 1% of all mobile searches in the United Kingdom and Germany and 2% of mobile searches in the United States. Similarly, DuckDuckGo makes up about 2% of all desktop searches within the United Kingdom and Germany and about 3% within the US.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-market-share.webp" alt="chart showing duckduckgo market share across us, germany and uk" width="936" height="513" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79528" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-market-share.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-market-share-480x263.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Roughly 58% of all of DuckDuckGo‚Äôs searches come from the United States. DuckDuckGo‚Äôs major international markets are in Europe, Canada, and Australia‚Äîwhere it receives 22%, 3%, and 2% of its remaining traffic, respectively.</p>
<div id="are-people-using-only-duckduckgo"></div>
<h3>5. Are people using only DuckDuckGo to search?</h3>
<p>The primary reason people start using DuckDuckGo is because they want the privacy that they can‚Äôt get from other search engines, browsers, and email services. DuckDuckGo isn‚Äôt the default search engine or browser on any device‚Äîsearchers generally have to manually update their preferences to make the switch to DuckDuckGo. Given that active decision‚Äîmost users don‚Äôt readily switch between the privacy-focused search engine and its traditional competitors. Three-quarters of DuckDuckGo searchers don‚Äôt use Google search at all and 69% don‚Äôt use Bing either.</p>
<p>This means that these searches on DuckDuckGo are a unique audience that you simply cannot reach if you‚Äôre simply just advertising on Google Ads.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-reach.webp" alt="chart showing duckduckgo reach" width="936" height="480" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79529" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-reach.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/duckduckgo-reach-480x246.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="üõë" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Worried you&#8217;re wasting spend in Google Ads? Find out with a free, instant audit &gt;&gt; <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader">Google Ads Performance Grader</a></p>
<div id="how-to-advertise-on-duckduckgo"></div>
<h2>How to advertise on DuckDuckGo</h2>
<p>The growing DuckDuckGo audience of affluent, privacy-concerned searchers that can no longer be found on Google or Bing is a valuable one that marketers will want to reach. DuckDuckGo prominently displays paid search ads atop their SERP like other search engines, but it doesn‚Äôt have its own ad platform like Google or Bing. Instead, DuckDuckGo partners directly with Microsoft Advertising as an exclusive premium search partner.</p>
<p>To advertise on the DuckDuckGo SERP, first create a <a href="https://ads.microsoft.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Microsoft Advertising</a> account. Then, create a new search campaign or <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/07/25/bing-ads-scheduled-imports">import your current Google Ads campaigns into Microsoft Advertising</a>. Finally, when setting up your ad groups, be sure to select your ad distribution settings to show your ads across the entire Microsoft Advertising network.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/how-to-advertise-on-duckduckgo.webp" alt="screenshot showing how to enable advertising on duckduckgo" width="936" height="406" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-79530" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/how-to-advertise-on-duckduckgo.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/how-to-advertise-on-duckduckgo-480x208.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f440.png" alt="üëÄ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Looking for more ways to drive people to your site? <strong>Free guide &gt;&gt;</strong> <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsite25WaysIncreaseTraffic.html?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_25WaysIncreaseTraffic_Download">25 Ways to Increase Traffic to Your Website</a></p>
<h2>Give it a go with DuckDuckGo?</h2>
<p>While it‚Äôs not likely that users will flee Google for this newer search engine, it‚Äôs important to know the key players in the search engine game. This is especially true as advertisers and marketers look for ways to reach users no matter where they‚Äôre searching online, making DuckDuckGo a potential place for you to expand your audience and reach.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/what-is-duckduckgo">Is DuckDuckGo Legit? 5 Facts That Prove It Is</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>Google Adds Search Themes to Performance Max: What You Need to Know</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/12/11/search-themes-for-performance-max-campaigns</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Mark Irvine]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 11 Dec 2023 12:30:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Paid Search Marketing]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=78419</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>We're breaking down all the details!</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/12/11/search-themes-for-performance-max-campaigns">Google Adds Search Themes to Performance Max: What You Need to Know</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>When Google first introduced its Performance Max campaigns, it set off with a goal to make advertising across all of its properties (search, display, video, Discover, Gmail, and Maps) simple to manage within one campaign type.</p>
<p>Getting started with Performance Max campaigns is easy. Optimizing Performance Max campaigns? Well, that can be much more difficult.</p>
<p>Luckily, Google recently released a new beta feature for Performance Max campaigns called ‚Äú<a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/14179631?sjid=9794266004901960563-NA" target="_blank" rel="noopener">search themes</a>‚Äù designed to help advertisers better target their ads with a similar keyword-inspired approach that most advertisers are used to. In this article, we‚Äôre covering what search themes are, how to create them, and how to use them the right way.</p>
<h3>Table of contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#what-are-search-themes">What are search themes for Performance Max campaigns?</a></li>
<li><a href="#search-themes-to-replace-custom-segments">Search themes will replace custom segments based on search intent</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-to-create-search-themes">How do I create search themes?</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-search-themes-impact-search-ads">How will search themes affect my search ads?</a></li>
<li><a href="#best-practices-for-search-themes">Best practices for using search themes in Performance Max campaigns</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="what-are-search-themes"></div>
<h2>What are search themes for Performance Max campaigns?</h2>
<p>Google‚Äôs fully automated campaign type allows you to control very little. You can improve your different ad assets, website, product feed, and even provide audience signals to better target your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/04/20/performance-max-pros-cons">Performance Max campaign</a>s‚Äìbut that‚Äôs still very lacking to the rest of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/09/21/google-ads-audience-targeting-cheat-sheet">Google Ad‚Äôs targeting options</a>. Especially for most of us who are used to running search campaigns with robust <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/keyword-match-types">keyword targeting options</a>‚Äìrunning search ads through <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-performance-max-pre-launch-optimizations">Performance Max</a> campaigns can be a frustrating experience.</p>
<p>Search themes are a new feature that allows advertisers to provide some additional context and signals to Google to help target their <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-performance-max-updates-2024">Performance Max</a> campaigns. Advertisers can provide search themes to Google to share how they expect their customers to search for their products or services.</p>
<p>With this additional context, Google can consider these search themes as new signals to target audiences based on their search behavior. Google may use these search themes to better <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/performance-max">refine their Performance Max</a> campaign targets, or to reach new relevant placements on the SERP and beyond.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-performance-max.webp" alt="google ads search themes in performance max campaigns" width="845" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78423" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-performance-max.webp 845w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-performance-max-480x341.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 845px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Search themes is an optional feature in Performance Max campaigns. However, we‚Äôve seen time and time again that Performance Max campaigns perform the best when they‚Äôre given better signals, so I‚Äôd encourage you to provide Google with at least a few search themes to give Google enough signals to optimize your campaigns with. Advertisers can provide up to 25 search themes per asset group.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="üõë" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Worried you&#8217;re wasting spend in Google Ads? Find out with a free, instant audit &gt;&gt; <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader">Google Ads Performance Grader</a></p>
<div id="search-themes-to-replace-custom-segments"></div>
<h2>Search themes are set to replace custom segments based on search intent</h2>
<p>Within Google‚Äôs most recent announcement introducing Search themes, Google also shares that they‚Äôll be ending support for <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/10/18/google-ads-custom-segments">custom segments</a> based on past search activity within Performance Max campaigns in early 2024. These audience segments will automatically be upgraded to Search Themes.</p>
<p>Previously known as ‚ÄúCustom Intent‚Äù audiences, these audiences used very similar signals to the new Search themes, effectively targeting people based on their past searches on Google. Since this audience signal is so similar to Google‚Äôs new ‚Äúsearch themes‚Äù beta, the automatic upgrade in 2024 is unlikely to negatively impact campaign performance. Hopefully, it streamlines workflows and makes signal management easier for advertisers.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-custom-segment.webp" alt="google ads search themes in performance max replacing custom segments" width="753" height="598" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78424" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-custom-segment.webp 753w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-custom-segment-480x381.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 753px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Custom segments based on previous search activities will continue to function uninterrupted in other campaign types, including search campaigns. Additionally, all other custom segments based on other attributes (affinities, interests, apps, URLs, and demographics) will continue to exist in Performance Max campaigns and serve as valuable audience signals for Google‚Äôs ongoing optimization.</p>
<div id="how-to-create-search-themes"></div>
<h2>How do I create search themes in my Performance Max campaigns?</h2>
<p>Search themes is a new feature in beta and may not currently be available to all advertisers, however, Google is expected to release it to more advertisers throughout the rest of the year.</p>
<ol>
<li>To add search themes to your Performance Max campaigns, simply:<br />
Select a Performance Max campaign.</li>
<li>Select an Asset group. Each asset group can have different audience signals and search themes.</li>
<li>Next to your ad assets in your Asset group, you‚Äôll notice a card for ‚ÄúSignals.‚Äù Select the pencil icon to edit your signals.<img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-audience-signals.webp" alt="how to set up search themes in performance max - signals audience segment" width="648" height="502" class="aligncenter wp-image-78425" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-audience-signals.webp 648w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-audience-signals-480x372.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 648px, 100vw" /></li>
<li>Here, you‚Äôll see the new Search Themes beta. Advertisers can add up to 25 unique search themes per asset group to help improve the signals of their Performance Max campaign. Each search theme must be shorter than 80 characters in length.<img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-setup.webp" alt="google ads search themes set up in performance max" width="936" height="286" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78426" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-setup.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-setup-480x147.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></li>
<li>Be sure to scroll to the bottom of the page and save your changes to your Asset group signals!</li>
</ol>
<p>Search themes can also be edited or removed at any time from this menu. Once changed or removed, Google will no longer use that signal when targeting its ads to an audience.</p>
<p>But removing a search theme isn‚Äôt like removing a keyword or <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/negative-keywords">adding a negative keyword</a> in a search campaign‚ÄìGoogle may continue to serve ads on similar search queries if it believes it‚Äôs relevant to users. However, Search themes will still respect any brand exclusions or account-level negative keywords that you‚Äôve implemented. If you want to prevent your Performance Max campaigns from serving for irrelevant and unwanted traffic&#8211;you‚Äôll still want to use those tools!</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/26a1.png" alt="‚ö°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Is your Google Ads account set up for success? Download now &gt;&gt; <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLAccountStructure.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_LastAccountStructureGuide_Download">The Last Guide to Google Ads Account Structure You&#8217;ll Ever Need</a></p>
<div id="how-search-themes-impact-search-ads"></div>
<h2>How will search themes in Performance Max campaigns affect my search ads?</h2>
<p>Performance Max campaigns and traditional search campaigns are both eligible to serve ads on the Google SERP and search partner engines. Advertisers who are running both Performance Max campaigns and search campaigns will often run into issues where both campaign types are targeting the same searches and risk serving different ad experiences to the same searches or struggle to manage the two campaigns synchronously. Using search themes in Performance Max may ease some of those issues for advertisers.</p>
<p>In these issues where multiple campaigns or ad groups are eligible to serve an ad to a searcher, <a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/2756257?sjid=9794266004901960563-NA" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google prioritizes exact match keywords</a> that are identical to the search above all others. Google‚Äôs new Search themes are treated as a lower priority, equal to that of phrase and broad match keywords.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-match-types.webp" alt="google ads search themes - match types prioritized in google ads" width="936" height="504" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-78427" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-match-types.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/google-ads-search-themes-match-types-480x258.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Your exact match keywords in your search campaigns will also take priority over your Performance Max campaigns‚Äìso they‚Äôre still a must-have for advertisers now.</p>
<div id="best-practices-for-search-themes"></div>
<h2>Best practices for using search themes in Performance Max campaigns</h2>
<p>While nearly all additional data and context will help these Performance Max campaigns continue to improve, advertisers can make the most of search themes in their accounts by following a few tips.</p>
<h3>1. Use search themes to provide information missing from your landing pages</h3>
<p>If you‚Äôve just launched a new product or website, your landing page may not include every single feature, benefit, use, value, and detail that a searcher might consider‚Äìand that‚Äôs okay! In fact, a clean and simplified <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/landing-page-optimization">landing page may help more people convert</a> on your site.</p>
<p>If Google can‚Äôt find that context from your landing page‚Äìfret not. Liberally use search themes in your Performance Max campaigns to provide those extra signals to Google so it best understands what your audience may be looking for and can optimize its placements accordingly.</p>
<h3>2. Be direct‚Äîespecially when using ulterior brand messaging</h3>
<p>What does direct mean? Well, consider the well-known fast-casual restaurant Hooters. If you were to just read their website or its descriptions, you might mistakenly describe their business as a chicken wings restaurant. But we all know that there are a few missing keywords in that description that serve their core value prop and distinguish them from similar competitors.</p>
<p>There‚Äôs nothing shameful about having hidden benefits that you don‚Äôt expressly convey within your ads or on your website. Maybe your hotel welcomes all but is known best for catering to families, tourists, a religious community, foreign-speaking nationals, or people recovering from a nearby medical procedure, or maybe it has a history of being haunted. You might not want to explicitly write some of that on your website or within your ads‚Äîbut if someone is specifically looking for a paranormal vacation a Sabbath-friendly accommodation, or a sanctuary nearby their treatment, advertisers can use search themes to better signal their ads within a Performance Max campaign.</p>
<h3>3. Maximize your varied and unique search themes</h3>
<p>Advertisers are allowed up to 25 search themes within each asset group. Generally, the more signals you can provide to Google, the better your Performance Max campaigns will perform. However, quantity isn‚Äôt the only factor in quality.</p>
<p>Treat your search themes similar to how you‚Äôd treat broad match keywords in your search campaigns‚Äìmake sure that they aren‚Äôt effectively the same signal. For example, the search themes ‚Äúcar‚Äù and ‚Äúautomobile‚Äù will reach the exact same audience and won‚Äôt improve performance incrementally.</p>
<h3>4. Consider competitor terms as search themes</h3>
<p>Especially if you‚Äôre a new brand on the market‚Äìthis will help Google more quickly understand who your prospects are currently searching for. <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/06/12/bidding-on-competitor-brands">Google allows bidding on your competitors&#8217; keywords</a> (in many cases) within your search campaigns and includes your competitor&#8217;s brands and product names as search themes. Before implementing this strategy, however, make sure that you understand any local laws or regulations about how you can advertise on competitor brands and trademarks.</p>
<h3>5. Use traditional search campaigns alongside your Performance Max campaigns</h3>
<p>Search themes are a powerful signal to add to your Performance Max campaigns. Even though your Performance Max campaigns will automatically target the search network, don‚Äôt neglect the importance of your search campaigns on their own.</p>
<p>Use search themes within your Performance Max campaigns to find new placements and scale incremental traffic and continue to apply that found insight to your search campaigns. As you build your search campaigns, be sure to incorporate exact match keywords so that they take priority over your Performance Max search theme signals, and you can continue to target, optimize, and refine your newfound traffic.</p>
<h2>Use search themes the right way in Performance Max campaigns</h2>
<p>Google‚Äôs new search themes beta will help advertisers share their human expertise and provide better signals to their machine learning powered Performance Max campaigns. Search themes gives you a little more control over your Performance Max campaigns, making them more effective and tailored for your audience.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/12/11/search-themes-for-performance-max-campaigns">Google Adds Search Themes to Performance Max: What You Need to Know</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>Google Ads Location Targeting: 5 Big Mistakes to Avoid</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/10/17/google-ads-location-targeting</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Mark Irvine]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 17 Oct 2023 12:30:43 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Local Marketing]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Paid Search Marketing]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=76508</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Don't make these mistakes when it comes to targeting the right location(s) for your Google Ads!</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/10/17/google-ads-location-targeting">Google Ads Location Targeting: 5 Big Mistakes to Avoid</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It can be challenging for local businesses to break through and get found‚Äìparticularly online. Local SEO has grown in importance over the past few years for businesses who want to dominate the SERPs within a particular city or region. But even with the best SEO strategy, you&#8217;re still not likely to own the first (or second, or third!) spot for local searches&#8211;especially those with purchase intent. Those belong to local search ads.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/SEO-vs-SEM-landscape.jpg" alt="SEO vs. SEM - google results showing ads" width="767" height="588" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76378" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/SEO-vs-SEM-landscape.jpg 767w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/SEO-vs-SEM-landscape-480x368.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 767px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Every result above the fold is a paid search result.</em></p>
<p>But showing up in these coveted spots requires expertise in a number of areas. You need to bid on the right keywords, have the right ad strategy, and target the right locations.</p>
<p>That‚Äôs where it pays to understand how to optimize your Google Ads location targeting. In this post, we‚Äôre covering:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="#google-ads-location-targeting-pitfalls">5 common pitfalls to avoid when setting your Google Ads location targeting</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-to-analyze-google-ads-location-performance">How to analyze your location performance in Google Ads</a></li>
<li><a href="#how-to-optimize-google-ads-location-performance">How to optimize your location performance with bid adjustments in Google Ads</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Let‚Äôs begin!</p>
<div id="google-ads-location-targeting-pitfalls"></div>
<h2>5 common pitfalls of setting your Google Ads location targeting</h2>
<p>When you create a campaign in Google Ads, you have near-limitless location targeting options to choose from. Targeting the whole world, country, state, city, or zip code‚Äìthe steps are easy and nearly identical.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-setup.webp" alt="google ads location targeting set up" width="936" height="383" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76512" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-setup.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-setup-480x196.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>But that simplicity and ease with endless choice often cause advertisers to make mistakes before their first ads are even live.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="üõë" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Worried you&#8217;re making more mistakes in Google Ads? Find out with a free, instant audit &gt;&gt; <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader">Google Ads Performance Grader</a></p>
<h3>1. Don‚Äôt make decisions with your gut!</h3>
<p>All humans are biased, and we over-appreciate our own experiences. Don‚Äôt let your experiences blind your marketing. You‚Äôre likely the most experienced searcher regarding your own business‚Äìand your prospective customers certainly have a different background than you.</p>
<p>You might assume that only people in your business‚Äôs town or neighborhood would become customers. Still, you might be surprised at how far people are prepared to travel to find a dentist, doctor, or lawyer they trust (or how far they‚Äôll travel to get away from the options in their own backyards!).</p>
<p>Instead of considering just your immediate area, view data within <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/02/17/ga4-features-for-advertisers">Google Analytics</a> to see where past visitors came from and how well they converted on your site. You may be surprised to see how intentionally people might search for your business, even several cities or states away.</p>
<h3>2. Don‚Äôt target areas based on their demographic profile</h3>
<p>You see your customers every day, and you likely know them the best! <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/11/target-audience">Understanding your target audience</a> will be key to building your campaigns, but it might lead you astray when setting up your location-targeting settings. Towns and cities might have very different demographic profiles, but none are strictly homogenous. Even if your target audience is more concentrated in one area, they will search for you wherever they are.</p>
<p>Instead of strictly targeting areas based on their demographic profile, consider improving your ads to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/10/31/detailed-demographics">target users based on their demographics</a> and other audience signals.</p>
<h3>3. Don‚Äôt over-rely on your CRM data for your customers‚Äô locations</h3>
<p>If you‚Äôre <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/customer-data/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">collecting data</a> from your past customers‚Äìyou‚Äôre setting yourself up to make better decisions in both your business and advertising. But when it comes to their customers&#8217; location data in your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/11/09/crm-for-small-business">CRM</a>, take that with a grain of salt.</p>
<p>Remember that their home address isn‚Äôt always where they‚Äôre searching. Especially since <a href="https://www.oberlo.com/blog/google-search-statistics" target="_blank" rel="noopener">nearly two-thirds</a> of searches in the US are coming from mobile devices, your customers are likely finding you while they‚Äôre searching at home, at work, and everywhere else they go.</p>
<p>Your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/04/12/first-party-data">first-party customer data</a> is among the most powerful tools to optimize your Google Ads campaigns.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/types-of-customer-data.webp" alt="types of customer data" width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76534" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/types-of-customer-data.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/types-of-customer-data-480x308.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Use your CRM data to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2016/10/21/calculate-roi-offline-transactions">measure offline conversions</a> and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/11/02/adwords-customer-match-setup">create customized audiences with Customer Match</a>. But when setting up location targeting, use your customer‚Äôs location data as a starting point for your analysis, not the end.</p>
<h3>4. Be cautious of radius targeting</h3>
<p>A common approach for many local businesses is to set their campaigns‚Äô location as a few-mile radius around their storefront. It‚Äôs a simple approach that can help you ensure that you‚Äôre reaching your local audience in all directions.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-radius-targeting.webp" alt="google ads location targeting - radius targeting setup screen" width="738" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76513" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-radius-targeting.webp 738w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-radius-targeting-480x390.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 738px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>But <a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/1722043?hl=en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">radius targeting</a> is deceptively simple‚Äìsetting a radius of ‚Äúa few miles‚Äù can quickly escalate to your ads reaching a much larger audience than you intended. Agreeing to ‚Äútarget a 10-mile radius‚Äù might quickly sound like it‚Äôs twice the area of ‚Äútargeting a 5-mile radius‚Äù‚Äìbut it‚Äôs actually not. That 10-mile radius area is <strong><em>four times as large</em></strong> as that 5-mile radius area. Remember‚Äìa circle&#8217;s area grows exponentially with its radius&#8217;s size!</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-area-of-circle.webp" alt="google ads location targeting - radius of circle" width="448" height="314" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76514" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-area-of-circle.webp 448w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-area-of-circle-300x210.webp 300w" sizes="(max-width: 448px) 100vw, 448px" /></p>
<p>Be aware of that verbal trick when you set up your radius targeting. Even if unintentional, your agency or marketing team may increase your reach (and necessary budget) significantly more than you first hear.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-increase-radius.webp" alt="google ad location targeting - increase radius" width="936" height="266" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76515" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-increase-radius.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-increase-radius-480x136.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Of course, the opposite is also true. If you‚Äôre a <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/12/09/free-and-low-budget-marketing-ideas">local business with a limited budget</a>, an effective way to reign in your campaigns‚Äô needed budget is simply to reduce the size of your targeting radius. This verbal trick can be a sneaky way to get a proud business owner or stakeholder to agree to a significant cut in their campaign‚Äôs ambitious reach without sounding like you‚Äôre cutting your targeting too much.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-decrease-targeting.webp" alt="google ads location targeting - decrease location targeting" width="936" height="252" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76516" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-decrease-targeting.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-decrease-targeting-480x129.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>5. Revisit your targeting regularly</h3>
<p>Once your campaigns are up and running, it‚Äôs easy not to look back at their settings. After all, campaigns require enough <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/adwords-optimization">regular review and optimization</a> of their keywords, negative keywords, ads, assets, bids, and account structure. But still, too many advertisers never revisit the location settings they launched their campaigns with. Even if perfect at the time‚Äìpeople move, cities change, and how people search evolves.</p>
<p>Make it a point to review and revisit your location targeting in your campaigns at least every six months. A campaign that is performing well may be worth expanding into some new areas. Or a campaign that is struggling may have too ambitious reach as-is.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4a1.png" alt="üí°" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Free guide &gt;&gt;</strong> <a href="https://marketing.wordstream.com/WSContentDLWebBlogInContentTextLinkTrickstoClicks.html?cid=Web_Blog_InContent_TextLink_TrickstoClicks_Download">10 Tricks to Get the Click: How to Write Exceptional Ad Copy</a></p>
<div id="how-to-analyze-google-ads-location-performance"></div>
<h2>How to analyze your location performance in Google Ads</h2>
<p>Over the years, Google has changed and hidden its reporting for how your ads perform in different geos. Luckily, you can still see exactly where your ads show the most, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/05/15/google-ads-benchmarks">their costs</a>, and conversions across different geographic areas.</p>
<h3>1. Using the Google Ads location report</h3>
<p>The most straightforward place to start is the most obvious. The locations report directly within Google Ads is readily accessible from the left-hand menu in a campaign. Sometimes hidden at the bottom of the bar, click ‚ÄúLocations &gt; Locations,‚Äù and you‚Äôll see a standard report that includes each targeting region you typed into your campaign settings.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-location-report.webp" alt="google ads location report for location targeting" width="936" height="341" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76517" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-location-report.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-location-report-480x175.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>If you‚Äôve only created one location target in your campaign, this is a trivial report as-is. Even if you were to include several, many advertisers get limited value from this screen.</p>
<p><strong>Let me tell you the trick.</strong> Check off all your targeted locations, and now a new option appears for ‚ÄúNarrow by.‚Äù Click Narrow by‚Äìand you‚Äôll be amazed at the specificity you can break your Google Ads geo data down. You can break this national data down to the state, county, city, or zip code. Furthermore, you can see data on unique areas like Congressional districts or Nielsen DMAs or areas of interest like Airports and Universities.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-narrow-location.webp" alt="narrow location in google ads location report" width="561" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76518" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-narrow-location.webp 561w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-narrow-location-480x513.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 561px, 100vw" /></p>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f9f1.png" alt="üß±" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Build a solid foundation for your campaigns with our free guide &gt;&gt; <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLAccountStructure.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_LastAccountStructureGuide_Download">The Last Guide to Google Account Structure You&#8217;ll Ever Need</a></div></div>
<h3>2. Using the Google Ads distance report</h3>
<p>The Google Ads distance report is particularly useful to advertisers who use radius targeting. If you‚Äôre unsure how large a radius your campaigns should target, the distance report will become your best tool. To access the <a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/2453994?hl=en#:~:text=Distance%20reports&amp;text=Your%20data%20will%20be%20organized,or%20content%20they'd%20viewed." target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads distance report</a>, select the ‚ÄúReports‚Äù icon in the top right corner of Google Ads. From there, select ‚ÄúPredefined reports (Dimensions)‚Äù &gt; ‚ÄúLocations‚Äù &gt; ‚ÄúDistance.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-distance-report.webp" alt="google ads location targeting - distance report" width="936" height="377" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76519" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-distance-report.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-distance-report-480x193.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>The Google Ads distance report will show how your ads perform at different distances from your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2011/09/19/adwords-location-extensions-guide">Location Assets (formerly Location Extensions)</a>. You can customize the columns to include relevant metrics or further segment the data.</p>
<p>Bear in mind that this report shows cascading radii that grow in size as you get further from your business. Each row‚Äôs data includes the one above it‚Äìi.e., the data from ‚ÄúWithin 5 miles‚Äù is also counted in the row for ‚ÄúWithin 10 miles.‚Äù</p>
<p>To see how searchers behave within these ranges, you can easily export this data into Looker Studio or Excel for quick manipulation. Once exported, some simple subtraction can help you understand how people search and convert at different distances from your location. To know how your ads are performing between 1 and 5 miles away, subject the data in the ‚ÄúWithin 1 mile‚Äù row of the location report from the data ‚ÄúWithin 5 miles.‚Äù Repeat that process for further distances, and you‚Äôll begin to see how far is ‚Äútoo far‚Äù for your local searchers.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-distance-from-location.webp" alt="google ads location targeting spreadsheet" width="936" height="479" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76521" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-distance-from-location.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-distance-from-location-480x246.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="how-to-optimize-google-ads-location-performance"></div>
<h2>How to optimize your location performance with bid adjustments in Google Ads</h2>
<p>Now that you have more insight into how your ads perform in different areas, you can <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/07/google-ads-geotargeting">optimize your targeting</a>. Some easy wins might be to expand your reach by targeting neighboring regions or reducing wasted spend from areas that haven‚Äôt converted well for you. But don‚Äôt get hung up on the binaries of just targeting or excluding‚Äìyou can use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2013/08/05/geotargeting-with-bid-modifiers">location bid adjustments </a>to bid more aggressively for areas near your business where you expect local users to be easier to convert and reduce your bids as a searcher is further away.</p>
<p>Using location bid adjustments, you can still reach audiences far away while prioritizing your spend and focus on a hyper-specific local market.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-optimization.webp" alt="google ads location targeting bid optimization" width="936" height="532" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-76522" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-optimization.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/google-ads-location-targeting-optimization-480x273.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h1>Optimize your Google Ads location targeting with ease</h1>
<p>It can be intimidating for local businesses to choose where to target their <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/learn/ppc101">PPC campaigns</a>. Google Ads offers advertisers a lot of choice, and it can often feel like you‚Äôre risking your limited budget by targeting an area too wide or too far from your backyard.</p>
<p>Luckily, savvy advertisers know how to find data hidden within these geographic reports and use it to find new opportunities to reach prospective customers and minimize your wasted ad spend.</p>
<p>Here are those five <a href="https://www.link-assistant.com/news/top-search-engines.html">mistakes</a> to avoid when it comes to Google Ads location targeting:</p>
<ol>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Don‚Äôt make decisions with your gut!</span></li>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Don‚Äôt target areas based on their demographic profile</span></li>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Don‚Äôt over-rely on your CRM data for your customers‚Äô locations</span></li>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Be cautious of radius targeting</span></li>
<li class="p1"><span class="s1">Revisit your targeting regularly</span></li>
</ol>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/10/17/google-ads-location-targeting">Google Ads Location Targeting: 5 Big Mistakes to Avoid</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>How to Run Microsoft Professional Service Ads (+How They Compare to Google Local Services Ads)</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/27/professional-service-ads</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Mark Irvine]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 27 Sep 2023 12:30:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Paid Search Marketing]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=75659</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Get the latest on this ad type just for service-based businesses from Microsoft Advertising.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/27/professional-service-ads">How to Run Microsoft Professional Service Ads (+How They Compare to Google Local Services Ads)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Lots of industries can struggle with PPC, but it can feel the hardest when you‚Äôre a small business trying to promote your professional services in a small market. Large brands can easily outspend you and dominate search results&#8211;so showing up and sticking out as a local expert can be a real challenge.</p>
<p>Luckily, Microsoft Advertising has an ad type called Professional Service Ads to help advertisers promote their expertise in their target markets. We&#8217;re going to cover everything you need to know about this ad type in this article.</p>
<h3>Table of contents</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="#definition">What are Professional Service Ads?</a></li>
<li><a href="#industries">What industries can use Professional Service Ads?</a></li>
<li><a href="#differences">Microsoft Professional Service Ads vs. Google Local Services Ads</a></li>
<li><a href="#howto">How to get started with Microsoft Professional Service Ads</a></li>
<li><a href="#bestpractices">Professional Service Ads best practices</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="definition"></div>
<h2>What are Professional Service Ads?</h2>
<p>Microsoft‚Äôs <a href="https://about.ads.microsoft.com/en-us/blog/post/march-2022/helping-better-connect-consumers-to-professionals?s_int=en-us-gct-web-src_msaweb-sub_blog-flx_professional" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Professional Service Ads</a> are designed to connect service providers to the searchers looking for their help. These ads appear on Bing when a user searches directly for a relevant professional, brand, or issue that they‚Äôre looking for help with. Unlike traditional search ads, Professional Service Ads will feature an image and professional details about the advertiser.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-example.jpg" alt="microsoft professional service ads example in serp" width="936" height="551" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75667" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-example.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-example-480x283.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>These new Professional Service Ads can show up atop the Bing SERP, within Bing Maps, and within the Bing Local Answer pack as well.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-placements.jpg" alt="microsoft professional service ads placements" width="936" height="554" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75668" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-placements.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-placements-480x284.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Professional Service Ads are designed with advertisers of all sizes in mind. Whether you‚Äôre running a one-man local practice, a regional branch, or a national brand, you can use Professional Service Ads to highlight the talent within your business and attract new customers from any market.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-use-cases.jpg" alt="best use cases for microsoft professional service ads " width="936" height="312" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75669" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-use-cases.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-use-cases-480x160.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Best of all, Microsoft‚Äôs Professional Service Ads can show alongside your existing search ads on the same SERP and compete in a different ad auction. This means these new Professional Service Ads could allow you to serve multiple ads on the same SERP and increase your visibility without increasing your current <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/11/06/bing-ads-performance-benchmarks">search ads‚Äô CPC</a>.</p>
<p>Professional Service Ads don‚Äôt require keywords or text ads. Instead, advertisers can provide important details about their services and business directly to Microsoft <a href="https://help.ads.microsoft.com/#apex/ads/en/60134/1">via a unique feed.</a> This allows them to customize how their ads show, what job types they can help with, and contact information for interested prospective clients.</p>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f928.png" alt="ü§®" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Curious about what kind of results you can get from search advertising? <a href="https://marketing.localiq.com/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteGoogleAdsBenchmarks2023.html?cid=Web_WS_incontent_guide_2023benchmarks_Download&amp;utm_source=wordstream&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=incontent_links">Download our search ads benchmarks</a> to find out!</div></div>
<div id="industries"></div>
<h2>What industries can use Professional Service Ads?</h2>
<p>Today, Microsoft Advertising supports Professional Service Ads for the following industries:</p>
<ul>
<li>Insurance Services</li>
<li>Tax Services</li>
<li>Real Estate Services</li>
<li><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/home-services-search-advertising-benchmarks/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Home Services</a></li>
<li>Doctor &amp; Clinic Ads</li>
</ul>
<p>Microsoft is expected to roll out Professional Service Ads to more industries throughout the year and has announced that Lawyer &amp; Legal Service Ads as well as Financial Advisor Ads are on their future roadmap.</p>
<div id="differences"></div>
<h2>Google Local Service Ads (LSAs) vs. Microsoft Professional Service Ads: What&#8217;s the difference?</h2>
<p>Microsoft‚Äôs newest ad format may look very familiar to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/06/11/google-local-service-ads">Google‚Äôs Local Service Ads</a> to most searchers. They both appear at the top of the SERP and the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/07/02/how-to-rank-higher-on-google-maps">local map pack</a> for relevant local searches and feature a photo, reviews, and the location of nearby advertisers. However, advertisers will notice some major differences between Google‚Äôs Local Services ads and Microsoft‚Äôs Professional Service Ads.</p>
<h3>1. Professional Service Ads have a simpler setup than LSAs</h3>
<p>Google‚Äôs Local Service Ads are a powerful tool but can be painful to set up. Not only do you have to create your own Local Service Ads business profile outside of Google Ads, but depending on your industry, you may have to submit additional license and insurance information and your team may need to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/google-guarantee/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">complete a series of background checks</a> from one of Google‚Äôs partners before your Local Service Ad ever shows.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/google-guarantee-promise-screenshot.jpg" alt="the google guarantee process is one difference between google local services ads and microsoft professional ads" width="936" height="431" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75670" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/google-guarantee-promise-screenshot.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/google-guarantee-promise-screenshot-480x221.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p>Microsoft‚Äôs Professional Services Ads are designed to be set up quickly and easily. You can create and manage these ads directly within your existing Microsoft Advertising account alongside your other search and audience campaigns. Professional Service Ads take data directly from a feed to serve and do not require a lengthy onboarding or <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/google-guarantee/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">verification proces</a>s like Google‚Äôs LSAs.</p>
<h3>2. Professional Service Ads have more flexible management and optimization</h3>
<p>Google‚Äôs Local Service Ads have a lot of reach and advertisers can freely control and update important parts of their ads, such as their weekly budget or job type. But LSA advertisers lack some of the freedom to optimize or update their Local Service Ads like they would any other Google Ads campaign. Google <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/09/03/google-search-terms-report-changes">doesn‚Äôt show any search terms</a> from their Local Service Ads and doesn‚Äôt allow negative keywords either. Optimizations like bid adjustments or even daily budgets are also not available for Local Service Ads.</p>
<p>Creating a Google Local Services Ad offers limited room for differentiation. Local Services Ads allow advertisers to <a href="https://support.google.com/localservices/answer/7549347?visit_id=638179642389787244-659734732&amp;hl=en&amp;rd=1">highlight limited information</a> from a checklist of options within their business bio. Google also has very strict <a href="https://support.google.com/localservices/answer/9091766">policies for your photos and headshots</a> which can leave even the most unique business serving nearly identical Local Service Ads to their competitors.</p>
<p>Microsoft‚Äôs Professional Services ads offer similar levels of control and optimization as their other search campaigns‚Äìwhich include the ability to set and control daily budgets, bid adjustments, review search terms, and add negative keywords.</p>
<p>Additionally, the business data feeds used for Microsoft‚Äôs Professional Service Ads allow advertisers to provide much more customized details to optimize their ads for specific job types, highlight different messages, or test more dynamic images to show alongside their ads.</p>
<h3>3. Differences in pricing</h3>
<p>Google‚Äôs Local Service Ads are unique from the rest of their search ads. Instead of being charged per every click, advertisers are charged per each lead that comes directly from their LSAs.</p>
<p>Microsoft‚Äôs Professional Service Ads are priced per ad click, like most of their other campaigns.</p>
<div id="howto"></div>
<h2>How to get started with Microsoft Professional Service Ads</h2>
<p>To get started, you‚Äôll first need to <a href="https://help.ads.microsoft.com/#apex/ads/en/60135/-1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">create a data feed for Microsoft‚Äôs Professional Service Ads</a>. For individual practitioners, this can be a simple spreadsheet that you upload once into Microsoft Advertising to get started. Larger organizations may need a more dynamic approach to creating and managing a feed as their team of professionals, services, and specialties continue to change.</p>
<p>This data feed is just a structured way to pass along details about your business to Microsoft so that it can better target your ad and make it easier for prospective clients to contact you. While it may seem overwhelmingly technical at first glance, most of the information within your feed is simple to provide, mundane, and trivial for most professionals.</p>
<h3>Create a Professional Service Ads feed</h3>
<ol>
<li>I recommend starting by downloading <a href="https://ui.ads.microsoft.com/campaign/vnext/feeds/dynamicdata?aid=141371798&amp;cid=251051268&amp;uid=98339929" target="_blank" rel="noopener">this template</a> from Microsoft. This includes all the required and optional attributes for these campaigns properly formatted and includes sample values for each attribute.</li>
<li>Start off first by filling in the required attributes, listed below.</li>
</ol>
<table>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Attribute</strong></td>
<td><strong>Description</strong></td>
<td><strong>Example</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Description</td>
<td>A short description of the company or professional.</td>
<td>Luxury real estate company</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Final URL </strong></td>
<td>The same domain as your website. Must begin with http:// or https://.</p>
<p>This will not be shown in the ad.</td>
<td>http://www.contoso.com/seattle/id</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>ID </strong></td>
<td>Unique ID of the item comprised of any sequence of letters and digits.</p>
<p>This will not be shown in the ad.</td>
<td>AB1234</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Name </strong></td>
<td>The name of the company or professional.</p>
<p>If it&#8217;s a professional, put first name + last name.</td>
<td>David Johnson</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Profession </strong></td>
<td>The type of profession.</p>
<p>This will not be shown in the ad. Instead, we&#8217;ll use this to match ads with terms people search for.</p>
<p><em>Note:</em> You must choose one of the following examples for your ad to serve.</td>
<td>Doctor &amp; clinic</p>
<p>Financial advisor</p>
<p>Insurance service</p>
<p>Real estate service</p>
<p>Tax service</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Target ad group</td>
<td>The name of the targeted Professional services ad group.</p>
<p>This will not be shown in the ad.</td>
<td>Real-Estate-Placement-AdGroup</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Target campaign </strong></td>
<td>The name of the targeted Professional services ads campaign.</p>
<p>This will not be shown in the ad.</td>
<td>Real_Estate</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<ol start="3">
<li>Provide as much relevant information on the optional attributes as possible. The more information you provide, the more detail that Microsoft has to optimize your Professional Service Ads targeting and trigger your ad for relevant searches.</li>
<li>Name your ‚Äútarget campaign(s)‚Äù and ‚Äútarget ad group(s).‚Äù These are required attributes that will need to match the name of the campaigns and ad groups you build later on. While most businesses may be able to run just one campaign with one ad group to launch their Professional Service Ads, if you ever want to structure your account to have multiple different campaigns or ad groups, you will need to update these attributes in your feed.</li>
</ol>
<p>You can update your feeds at any time to add new teammates, services, details, or adjust your account structure.</p>
<h3>Upload a Professional Services Ad feed</h3>
<p>Once you‚Äôve prepped your data feeds, save them as a CSV, TSV, XLSX, or ZIP file and log in to your Microsoft Advertising account.</p>
<ol>
<li>From the top menu in Microsoft Advertising, select &#8220;Tools&#8221; &gt; &#8220;Business data.&#8221;<img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-upload-data-feed.jpg" alt="microsoft professional service ads - add data feed" width="936" height="420" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75673" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-upload-data-feed.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-upload-data-feed-480x215.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></li>
<li>Here, from the left-hand menu, select ‚ÄúDynamic Data Feeds.‚Äù</li>
<li>Click on the blue ‚ÄúUpload‚Äù drop-down and select ‚ÄúProfessional Services.‚Äù<img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-dynamic-data-feeds.jpg" alt="microsoft professional service ads - dynamic data feed" width="424" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75674" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-dynamic-data-feeds.jpg 424w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/professional-service-ads-dynamic-data-feeds-212x300.jpg 212w" sizes="(max-width: 424px) 100vw, 424px" /></li>
<li>Name your data feed and select the file to upload. At this time, you can preview your feed to troubleshoot any issues and then upload the feed to Microsoft Advertising.</li>
<li>(Optional) If you anticipate that you‚Äôll be constantly updating this feed because your company has a large, dynamic team or because you will be making regular changes to your availability, you can schedule Microsoft to import a dynamic feed from a URL. Click on the recently uploaded feed and select ‚ÄúSchedules‚Äù to set a regular schedule for Microsoft to reimport this feed.</li>
</ol>
<h3>Create a Professional Service Ad campaign</h3>
<p>Once your Professional Service Feed is created and uploaded, creating a Professional Service campaign is very similar to your other Microsoft Advertising campaigns, with a few notable quirks.</p>
<ol>
<li>Create a new <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2013/11/21/ppc-keyword-research-guide">search campaign</a> and name it <em>exactly</em> as you‚Äôve named it within the ‚ÄúTarget Campaign‚Äù attribute within your feed. If this doesn‚Äôt match that attribute exactly, it will not serve any Professional Service Ads.</li>
<li>Follow the usual steps to set your campaign‚Äôs budget, location targeting, and other campaign settings. You can add a disclaimer to your ad during this process. Do <strong>not</strong> enable <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/07/10/dynamic-search-ads">dynamic search ads</a>.</li>
<li>Create your ad group and name it exactly as you‚Äôve named it within the ‚ÄúTarget Ad Group‚Äù attribute within your feed. Again, if this doesn‚Äôt match exactly, it will not serve any Professional Service Ads.</li>
<li>You‚Äôll need to create a ‚Äúplaceholder‚Äù keyword for this ad group. Professional Service Ads don‚Äôt use keywords to target their ads, but in order for the ad group to function, there needs to be an active keyword. I recommend creating a long-tailed exact-match keyword with no expected search volume to prevent this placeholder from serving ads.</li>
<li>You‚Äôll also need to create a ‚Äúplaceholder‚Äù Responsive Search Ad for the ad group. Similarly, this Responsive Search Ad will never show, but its Final URL will be featured as the Display URL within your Professional Search Ads. The headlines and descriptions, however, will not be included.</li>
<li>Hit save and launch your new Professional Services Ads!</li>
</ol>
<div id="bestpractices"></div>
<h2>Professional Service Ads best practices</h2>
<p>Ready to get started with Professional Service Ads? Use these best practices to make sure your campaigns are successful.</p>
<h3><strong></strong>1. Run Professional Service Ads along with traditional search campaigns</h3>
<p>Professional Service Ads should be treated as a great compliment to your search ads, not as a replacement. By running both simultaneously, you can have multiple ads appear on the same SERP and draw more attention to your practice. Since Professional Service Ads compete in a separate ad auction from text ads, you shouldn‚Äôt expect your search ads to have any change in performance by running Professional Service Ads.</p>
<h3><strong></strong>2. Start with the right budget</h3>
<p>Microsoft recommends that national brands looking to promote their services across the entirety of the United States should start with between $100-500 daily budget for their Professional Service Ads. Local businesses need much less budget to target their market. Microsoft recommends that local businesses start with 20% of their current PPC budget on Professional Service Ads for the markets they target.</p>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6d1.png" alt="üõë" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Worried you&#8217;re wasting spend in Google Ads? Find out once-and-for-all with our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader">Free Google Ads Performance Grader</a>!</div></div>
<h3><strong></strong>3. Pay attention to bidding</h3>
<p>Bidding is managed at the ad group level. To get started, Microsoft recommends using manual or enhanced <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/05/15/google-ads-benchmarks">CPC</a> bidding and setting the bid between $3-5 CPC. You can freely adjust this based on the performance of your ads.</p>
<h3><strong></strong>4. Review your search terms</h3>
<p>Unlike Google‚Äôs Local Search Ads, these Professional Service Ads will collect data on the search terms they triggered for as well as their associated costs and conversions. Without keywords in your Professional Service Ad campaigns, Microsoft may trigger your ads for some unexpected search terms, so plan to review your traffic regularly and add negative keywords as you see fit.</p>
<h3><strong></strong>5. Include audiences</h3>
<p>These Professional Service Ads allow you to refine your targeting with demographics and audiences, like your other search campaigns. You can use remarketing, in-market, custom audiences, or even <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/10/24/bing-ads-linkedin-profile-targeting">LinkedIn profile targeting</a> in Microsoft Advertising to target, exclude, or adjust your bids for more valuable prospects.</p>
<h2>Maximize Professional Service Ads performance</h2>
<p>This new ad type to Microsoft Advertising is an interesting one for many industries. There are certainly advantages to being an early adopter, too. <a href="https://about.ads.microsoft.com/en-us/blog/post/march-2022/helping-better-connect-consumers-to-professionals?s_int=en-us-gct-web-src_msaweb-sub_blog-flx_professional" target="_blank" rel="noopener">According to Microsoft</a>, Professional Service Ad campaigns on their network were already seeing:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>60% higher conversion rate</strong>, when compared to traditional search ads on their network.</li>
<li><strong>67% lower CPA, </strong>when compared to traditional search ads on their network.</li>
</ul>
<p>Those results may sound fantastic on their own‚Äìbut keep in most <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/11/06/bing-ads-performance-benchmarks">advertisers already see significantly lower CPC and CPA on Microsoft Advertising when compared to Google Ads</a>‚Äìso these new Professional Service Ads are even more powerful for advertisers to attract new clients.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/27/professional-service-ads">How to Run Microsoft Professional Service Ads (+How They Compare to Google Local Services Ads)</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>Google Ads Rolling Out Enhancements to Location Assets: Here&#8217;s How to Use It</title>
		<link>https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/07/google-ads-location-assets-enhancements</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Mark Irvine]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Sep 2023 13:30:41 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Google Ads]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Local Marketing]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/?p=75832</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Google Ads new enhancement to location assets pulls an image from a business's Google Business Profile into its ad. Find out how to use this enhancement (or how to opt out).</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/07/google-ads-location-assets-enhancements">Google Ads Rolling Out Enhancements to Location Assets: Here&#8217;s How to Use It</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Location Assets (formerly known as <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2011/09/19/adwords-location-extensions-guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Location Extensions</a>) have been a staple of any good local business‚Äôs Google Ads account for over a decade. Although their name has changed a few times since their introduction, they‚Äôve always functioned the same and served the same value‚Äìsimply link your Google Business Profile to Google Ads and your ads will begin to show your location to searchers nearby.</p>
<p>After decades of this simple but effective design, Google recently began automatically enhancing its location assets to <a href="https://support.google.com/google-ads/answer/2404182?utm_source=awfe&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=20249167#merchant_photos&amp;zippy=%2Copt-out-of-using-merchant-photos-in-local-ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">include an image of their local business</a> alongside their address and hours. This new feature is designed to help your ads stand out on the busy SERP, improve ad performance, and reinforce trust in your local business.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-example.jpg" alt="google ads location assets enhancements - example via google search" width="936" height="330" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75836" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-example.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-example-480x169.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em><a href="https://twitter.com/darcyburk/status/1674408251935318017/photo/2" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source</a></em></p>
<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll walk through:</p>
<ul>
<li>How to feature your business&#8217;s images in your Google Ads location assets</li>
<li>Best practices for your business&#8217;s images in location assets</li>
<li>How to opt out of showing your images in location assets</li>
</ul>
<p>Let&#8217;s get started.</p>
<h2>How to feature your business&#8217;s images in your Google Ads location assets</h2>
<p>To take advantage of this new feature, all advertisers need to do is maintain their Google Business Profile, have it linked to Google Ads, and have their location extensions active in their campaigns. Google will automatically highlight any of your Google Business Profile‚Äôs merchant photos.</p>
<p>Your Google Ads location <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-assets">assets</a> will only include images that you‚Äôve uploaded directly to your GBP‚Äôs Merchant Photos‚Äìit will not pull any photos submitted to your GBP from past visitors or from reviews, so you‚Äôll always set the right impression with your ads‚Äô images.</p>
<h3>1. Create and manage your Google Business Profile‚Äôs merchant photos</h3>
<p>For your Google Ads‚Äô location assets to feature your business‚Äôs images, you‚Äôll first need to upload at least one merchant photo to your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/08/what-is-google-my-business" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Business Profile</a>. To upload merchant photos, first sign into your Google Business Profile and select ‚ÄúAdd Photo.‚Äù</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-merchant-photo.jpg" alt="location assets google ads - where to manage images for merchant center" width="936" height="411" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75837" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-merchant-photo.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-merchant-photo-480x211.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>2. Upload your images</h3>
<p>You‚Äôll then have three options for the type of photo to upload.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Logo: </strong>Your logo photo will help you keep your brand consistent and identifiable across Google. Your logo icon will appear alongside any posts from your profile or anytime you respond to a question or review.</li>
<li><strong>Cover photo: </strong>Your cover photo is the money shot ‚Äì this photo is most likely to show up first in your Google Business Profile listing and will be used the most in your Google location assets images.</li>
<li><strong>Photo: </strong>These are supplementary photos that will show in your Google Business Profile listing. They‚Äôre often visible alongside your Cover photo, so it‚Äôs worth including at least several different and dynamic images of your business.</li>
</ul>
<h3>3. Remove outdated photos</h3>
<p>If your business photos are outdated or poor quality, you can also remove any old photos from your Google Business Profile. Just log into your Google Business Profile and select anywhere in the photos section. Navigate to the ‚ÄúBy owner‚Äù section and select the photo you wish to remove. In the top right corner, you should be able to select a trash can ‚Äúdelete‚Äù icon to remove it from your profile.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-remove-google-business-image.jpg" alt="location assets enhancement - remove google business image from profile" width="936" height="572" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75844" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-remove-google-business-image.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-remove-google-business-image-480x293.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6a8.png" alt="üö®" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Are your Google Ads missing the mark? Find out with a free, instant audit from our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Grader</a>!</div></div>
<h2>Best practices for Google Business Profile photos and Google Ads location assets</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/03/google-my-business-optimization">Optimizing your Google Business Profile</a> isn‚Äôt just important for your Google Ads location assets. Your Google Business Profile is likely the first thing searchers will see when they find you online, and it‚Äôs a huge part of Google‚Äôs own <a href="https://localiq.com/local-marketing-lab/seo/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">local SEO</a> ranking algorithm.</p>
<p>Spend the time to completely fill out your Google Business Profile and regularly update it to highlight to both Google and searchers alike that you‚Äôre an active, <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/how-to-respond-to-google-reviews-with-examples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">responsive</a>, and trustworthy business.</p>
<h3>1. Prioritize a high-quality cover photo</h3>
<p>Your cover photo will usually be shown first and most prominently on the SERP, alongside your GBP, and now alongside your Google Ads. Ensure that your cover photo best represents the image of your brand and is accurate to your business. Use proper lighting, focus, and minimal alterations. Google recommends your cover photo to be at least 720 x 720 in size.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-example-plumbing.jpg" alt="location assets enhancements - example of ad with image as part of location asset" width="936" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75848" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-example-plumbing.jpg 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-example-plumbing-480x308.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>2. Include a variety of different photos</h3>
<p>Your cover photo may get the most attention, but it won‚Äôt always show alone. A prospective visitor is likely to browse several images online before visiting in person. Consider including:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Several exterior images: </strong>To help customers recognize your business as they approach. Include different images to highlight how your storefront looks from different directions, parking and transit options, as well as how your business looks at night.</li>
<li><strong>Interior images: </strong>To highlight the atmosphere that customers should expect in your store. Highlight color product displays, seasonal areas, waiting rooms, common areas, and amenities that customers may want to see.</li>
<li><strong>Staff photos: </strong>To highlight your great team and present a more personal side of your business. Authentic photos that show your team working together earns trust in your business. Avoid including formal headshots.</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-best-practices-images.jpg" alt="example of google business images for boston real estate agent" width="533" height="598" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75846" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-best-practices-images.jpg 533w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-best-practices-images-480x539.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 533px, 100vw" /></p>
<div class='et-box et-shadow'>
					<div class='et-box-content'>Make sure your listings are up to par with LocaliQ&#8217;s <a href="https://localiq.com/free-business-listings-grader/?cid=Web_WS_InContentTextLink_Freemium_Listings&amp;utm_source=wordstream&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=freemium" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Free Business Listings Grader</a> <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2705.png" alt="‚úÖ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></div></div>
<h3>3. Create a Google Ads Logo asset</h3>
<p>Your Google Business Profile will highlight your logo alongside your posts and responses automatically. You also highlight that same logo alongside all your Google ads to reinforce your brand consistently on the SERP. Creating a logo asset is a simple and effective way to improve your ads performance, but you‚Äôll need to <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/07/13/google-advertiser-verification">verify your Google Ads account</a> before you can implement it.<img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-logo-asset.jpg" alt="location assets - google logo asset" width="701" height="600" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-75838" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-logo-asset.jpg 701w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/location-assets-enhancements-logo-asset-480x411.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 701px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>4. Enhance your ads with image assets</h3>
<p>Your location assets and images from your Google Business Profile will automatically appear when a user is searching for you locally‚Äìbut searchers outside of your area may not always see these assets.</p>
<p>Include <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/07/21/google-ads-image-extensions">image assets</a> in your Google Ads campaigns to provide more visual aspects to your search ads, whether or not a user is searching locally or not. Image assets are also more flexible and don‚Äôt need to be directly related to your physical location.</p>
<p>Use them to highlight images of more seasonal events, sales, products, and services that wouldn‚Äôt always be appropriate to be prominently displayed on your Google Business Profile.</p>
<h2>How to opt out of automatically including photos in your local Google Ads</h2>
<p>Some businesses won‚Äôt always have the most aesthetic Google Business Profile photos and may want to opt out of including photos of their location within Google Ads. Luckily for them, these new features for location assets can be turned off and allow advertisers to just show their location alongside their ad without any photos.</p>
<p>To opt out of automatically including photos in your local Google Ads, follow these steps:</p>
<ol>
<li>Within Google Ads, select ‚ÄúAds and Assets‚Äù from the left-hand bar, then select ‚ÄúAssets.‚Äù</li>
<li>Under the ‚ÄúAssociations view,‚Äù select the 3-dot ‚ÄúMore‚Äù icon. Then select ‚ÄúAccount-level automated assets.‚Äù</li>
<li>From this view, select the three-dot ‚ÄúMore‚Äù icon again. Now select the option ‚ÄúAdvanced settings‚Äù</li>
<li>Under ‚ÄúAutomatic locations,‚Äù there is a check box to ‚ÄúGrant Google Ads license to use merchant photos and other rich media from the linked Google Business Profiles in the advertising campaigns from this account.‚Äù Unselect this option and hit save. This will prevent Google from pulling any photos from your Google Business Profile to serve alongside your ads.</li>
</ol>
<h2>Show off your business images in location assets</h2>
<p>These new enhancements to location assets should be valuable for local advertisers and help their ads stick out from their competition on the SERP. As these features continue to roll out to more advertisers, now is a perfect time to <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/optimize-google-my-business-listing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">review your Google Business Profile</a> and ensure your business is prominently displayed in local searches.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/09/07/google-ads-location-assets-enhancements">Google Ads Rolling Out Enhancements to Location Assets: Here&#8217;s How to Use It</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
